    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Maps that represent the routes and other features of a transportation system; usually restricted to ground transportation although routes for ferries and other water transportation may be included.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000077178/Transportation Research Board, Smart Growth and Transportation (2005)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kaarten die de routes en andere kenmerken van een transportsysteem of wegennet vertegenwoordigen; meestal beperkt tot vervoer over land hoewel ook routes voor veerboten en ander vervoer over water kunnen worden opgenomen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Karte, die die Strecken und andere Eigenschaften eines Transportsystems darstellt; in der Regel beschränkt auf den Transport zu Land, allerdings können die Routen von Fähren oder anderen Wassertransportmitteln mit eingeschlossen sein.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
